Crowds gathered to watch the historic moment the world's last two airworthy Lancaster Bombers flew over Windermere today.

Spectators lined the shores of Windermere to see the momentous event of the two Second World War planes flying together.

The special flight was organised by Robert Johnstone as a surprise for his father, Archie, to celebrate what would have been the war veteran's 100th birthday.

